-- Zerah Declines to Three-Year Low as Regulator Halts Drilling
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-07-09T08:16:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-09/zerah-declines-to-three-year-low-as-regulator-halts-drilling.html
Zerah Oil & Gas Explorations LP (ZRAHL) 
dropped to the lowest level since 2009 after the Ramat-Gan,
Israel-based company said the regulator required it to halt
drilling at two sites in the 321/Zerah license.  The  shares  retreated 2.9 percent to 0.033 shekel, the
lowest level since June 2009, at 11:07 a.m. in Tel Aviv.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  